Privacy Policy for Serksa
Last Updated: April 18, 2025
Serksa ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application, Serksa (the "App"), an education technology platform designed to facilitate learning through interactive lessons, quizzes, and progress tracking. By using the App, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, please do not use the App.
1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information when you use Serksa:
a. Personal Information
Account Information: When you create an account, we may collect your name, email address, and other information you provide (e.g., username or profile details).

User-Generated Content: Information you input into the App, such as quiz responses, lesson progress, or notes.

b. Non-Personal Information
Usage Data: We collect information about how you interact with the App, such as pages viewed, features used, time spent, and actions taken (e.g., completing a lesson or quiz).

Device Information: We may collect details about your device, including device type, operating system, unique device identifiers, IP address, and mobile network information.

Analytics Data: We use third-party analytics tools (e.g., Firebase Analytics) to collect aggregated data about App usage to improve our services.

c. No Collection of Sensitive Data
Serksa does not collect sensitive personal information such as health data, financial information, or precise geolocation data unless explicitly stated and consented to by you.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:
Provide and personalize the App’s features, such as delivering educational content, tracking your learning progress, and recommending lessons.

Create and manage your account.

Communicate with you, including sending updates, notifications, or responding to inquiries.

Analyze usage trends to improve the App’s functionality and user experience.

Ensure the security and integrity of the App.

Comply with legal obligations.

3. How We Share Your Information
We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your information in the following cases:
Service Providers: We may share data with trusted third-party providers (e.g., cloud storage, analytics, or customer support services) to perform functions on our behalf. These providers are contractually obligated to protect your information.

Legal Requirements: We may disclose information if required by law, such as in response to a court order or to comply with regulatory obligations.

Business Transfers: If Serksa is involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.

4. Data Security
We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. For example, we use encryption for data in transit (e.g., HTTPS). However, no system is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
5. Your Choices and Rights
Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:
Access: Request a copy of the personal information we hold about you.

Correction: Request corrections to inaccurate or incomplete data.

Deletion: Request deletion of your personal information, subject to legal obligations.

Opt-Out: Opt out of certain data collection, such as analytics, where applicable.

To exercise these rights, contact us at [insert contact email, e.g., support@serksa.com]. We will respond within the timeframes required by applicable law.
6. Children’s Privacy
Serksa is not intended for children under the age of 13 (or the applicable age in your jurisdiction, e.g., 16 under GDPR). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under this age. If we learn that we have collected such information, we will take steps to delete it. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us at [insert contact email].
7. Third-Party Services
The App may integrate third-party services, such as analytics tools (e.g., Firebase Analytics) or cloud storage providers. These services may collect data as described in their respective privacy policies. We encourage you to review their policies:
Google Firebase Privacy Policy

8. Data Retention
We retain personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy or to comply with legal obligations. For example, account information is retained while your account is active, and usage data may be retained for analytics purposes. You may request deletion of your data as described in Section 5.
9. International Data Transfers
Your information may be stored or processed in servers located outside your country, including in the United States, where data protection laws may differ. We take steps to ensure adequate safeguards are in place for such transfers, such as Standard Contractual Clauses where required.
10. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of significant changes by posting the updated policy in the App or via email. The “Last Updated” date at the top indicates when the policy was last revised.
11. Contact Us
If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:
